## Registering fonts with R
# theme

theme_ms <- function(base_size = 10, base_family = "Arial") {
  library(grid)
  (theme_bw(base_size = base_size, base_family = base_family) +
      theme(
        text = element_text(color = "black"),
        axis.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = rel(1)),
        plot.title = element_text(face = "bold", size = rel(1)),
        axis.text = element_text(size = rel(1), color = "black"),
        legend.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
        legend.text = element_text(face = "bold"),
        legend.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent"),
        legend.key.size = unit(0.8, "lines"),
        panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", size = 1),
        panel.grid = element_blank()
      ))
}

# create a directory for saving figures
figsdir <- "./figures/"
if (!dir.exists(figsdir)) {
  dir.create(figsdir)
}

tabsdir <- "./tables/"
if (!dir.exists(tabsdir)) {
  dir.create(tabsdir)
}

# function to save figures
saveManuscriptPlot <- function(p, width, height) {
  figfile <- file.path(figsdir, sprintf(
    "%s.png",
    gsub("\\.", "_", deparse(substitute(p)))
  ))
  ggsave(figfile, plot = p, width = width, height = height, units = "in", device = "png")
  
  fill.gradient <- scale_fill_gradientn(
    colors = matlab.like(200),
    trans = "log10"
  )
}

4 pAAV2

4.1 Read Mapping

## Read Mapping

paav_mapping_data_unshifted <- read.table(file = "7/pAAV2bowtie2/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/mapping_rates.txt")

paav_mapping_data_unshifted <- paav_mapping_data_unshifted %>%
  mutate(
    sample_name = V1,
    Unmapped = V2 - V3,
    Duplicates = V4,
    Unique = V3 - V4
  ) %>%
  select(sample_name, Unmapped, Duplicates, Unique)

paav_mapping_data_unshifted <- paav_mapping_data_unshifted %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c("Unmapped", "Duplicates", "Unique"),
    names_to = "Variable",
    values_to = "Reads"
  )

paav_mapping_data_unshifted$Variable <- fct_relevel(factor(paav_mapping_data_unshifted$Variable), c("Unmapped", "Duplicates", "Unique"))

scientific <- function(x) {
  ifelse(x == 0, "0", parse(text = gsub("[+]", "", gsub("e", " %*% 10^", scientific_format()(x)))))
}

sample_order <- c("NGS1","NGS2","NGS3","NGS4","NGS5","NGS6","NGS7","NGS8")

paav_Fig1_read_mapping <- paav_mapping_data_unshifted %>%
  mutate(sample_name = case_when(
    sample_name == "NGS1_S1" ~ "NGS1",
    sample_name == "NGS2_S7" ~ "NGS2",
    sample_name == "NGS3_S2" ~ "NGS3",
    sample_name == "NGS4_S8" ~ "NGS4",
    sample_name == "NGS5_S3" ~ "NGS5",
    sample_name == "NGS6_S4" ~ "NGS6",
    sample_name == "NGS7_S5" ~ "NGS7",
    sample_name == "NGS8_S6" ~ "NGS8"
  )) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_name, y = Reads, fill = Variable)) +
  geom_bar(position = "stack", stat = "identity") +
  theme_ms() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(fill = "", y = "# Reads", x = "", title = "Read mapping of 1-8 with pAAV2") +
  theme(legend.position = "right") +
  scale_y_continuous(
    expand = c(0, 10000),
    labels = scientific
  ) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1")


saveManuscriptPlot(paav_Fig1_read_mapping, 10, 5)
paav_Fig1_read_mapping

4.2 Average sample coverage

# Setting up object
paav_average_cell_line_coverage <- read.table("7/pAAV2bowtie2/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/coverage/sample_depth", header = F)

paav_average_cell_line_coverage <- paav_average_cell_line_coverage %>%
  mutate(
    sample_name = as.factor(V1),
    average_coverage = V2
  ) %>%
  mutate(sample_name = case_when(
    sample_name == "NGS1_S1" ~ "NGS1",
    sample_name == "NGS2_S7" ~ "NGS2",
    sample_name == "NGS3_S2" ~ "NGS3",
    sample_name == "NGS4_S8" ~ "NGS4",
    sample_name == "NGS5_S3" ~ "NGS5",
    sample_name == "NGS6_S4" ~ "NGS6",
    sample_name == "NGS7_S5" ~ "NGS7",
    sample_name == "NGS8_S6" ~ "NGS8"
  )) %>%
  select(sample_name, average_coverage)


paav_average_cell_line_coverage$sample_name <- factor(paav_average_cell_line_coverage$sample_name, 
                                             levels = sample_order)

paav_Fig2_average_sample_coverage <- paav_average_cell_line_coverage %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_name, y = average_coverage)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "#377EB8") +
  labs(x = "", y = "Depth of Coverage", title = "Average sequencing depth for each sample") +
  theme_ms() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60, hjust = 1))

saveManuscriptPlot(paav_Fig2_average_sample_coverage, 10, 5)
paav_Fig2_average_sample_coverage

4.3 Perbase coverage

4.3.1 Unshifted average

paav_perbase_cell_files_unshifted <- list.files("7/pAAV2bowtie2/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/coverage/perbase_coverage/unshifted/", full.names = T)

paav_perbase_cell_files_shifted <- list.files("7/pAAV2bowtie2/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/coverage/perbase_coverage/shifted/", full.names = T)

paav_perbase_unshifted <- do.call("rbind", lapply(paav_perbase_cell_files_unshifted, function(fn) {
  data.frame(Filename = fn, read.table(fn))
})) %>%
  select(Filename, V2, V3) %>%
  mutate(
    perbase = V3,
    position = V2
  ) %>%
  mutate(Filename = str_remove(Filename, "7/pAAV2bowtie2/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/coverage/perbase_coverage/unshifted")) %>%
  mutate(Filename = str_remove(Filename, ".perbase.coverage")) %>%
  mutate(sample_name = case_when(
    Filename == "/NGS1_S1" ~ "NGS1",
    Filename == "/NGS2_S7" ~ "NGS2",
    Filename == "/NGS3_S2" ~ "NGS3",
    Filename == "/NGS4_S8" ~ "NGS4",
    Filename == "/NGS5_S3" ~ "NGS5",
    Filename == "/NGS6_S4" ~ "NGS6",
    Filename == "/NGS7_S5" ~ "NGS7",
    Filename == "/NGS8_S6" ~ "NGS8"
  )) %>%
  select(sample_name, position, perbase)

sample_order <- c("NGS1","NGS2","NGS3","NGS4","NGS5","NGS6","NGS7","NGS8")

paav_perbase_unshifted$sample_name <- factor(paav_perbase_unshifted$sample_name, 
                                             levels = sample_order)

paav_perbase_shifted <- do.call("rbind", lapply(paav_perbase_cell_files_shifted, function(fn) {
  data.frame(Filename = fn, read.table(fn))
})) %>%
  select(Filename, V2, V3) %>%
  mutate(
    perbase = V3,
    position = V2
  ) %>%
  mutate(Filename = str_remove(Filename, "7/pAAV2bowtie2/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/coverage/perbase_coverage/shifted")) %>%
  mutate(Filename = str_remove(Filename, ".perbase.coverage")) %>%
mutate(sample_name = case_when(
    Filename == "/NGS1_S1" ~ "NGS1",
    Filename == "/NGS2_S7" ~ "NGS2",
    Filename == "/NGS3_S2" ~ "NGS3",
    Filename == "/NGS4_S8" ~ "NGS4",
    Filename == "/NGS5_S3" ~ "NGS5",
    Filename == "/NGS6_S4" ~ "NGS6",
    Filename == "/NGS7_S5" ~ "NGS7",
    Filename == "/NGS8_S6" ~ "NGS8"
  )) %>%
  select(sample_name, position, perbase)

paav_perbase_shifted$sample_name <- factor(paav_perbase_shifted$sample_name, 
                                             levels = sample_order)

paav_Fig3_unshifted_average_perbase_coverage <- paav_perbase_unshifted %>%
  group_by(position) %>%
  summarise(mean_cov = mean(perbase)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = position, y = mean_cov)) +
  geom_line(color = "#377EB8") +
  labs(y = "Depth of Coverage", x = "pAAV2 position (bp)", title = "Average perbase coverage for NGS 1-8 against unshifted pAAV2") +
  theme_ms()
saveManuscriptPlot(paav_Fig3_unshifted_average_perbase_coverage, 10, 5)
paav_Fig3_unshifted_average_perbase_coverage

ph_mapping_data_unshifted <- read.table(file = "10/5-8plush/plotting_data/mapping_statistics/mapping_rates.txt")

ph_mapping_data_unshifted <- ph_mapping_data_unshifted %>%
  mutate(
    sample_name = V1,
    Unmapped = V2 - V3,
    Duplicates = V4,
    Unique = V3 - V4
  ) %>%
  select(sample_name, Unmapped, Duplicates, Unique)

ph_mapping_data_unshifted <- ph_mapping_data_unshifted %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c("Unmapped", "Duplicates", "Unique"),
    names_to = "Variable",
    values_to = "Reads"
  )

ph_mapping_data_unshifted$Variable <- fct_relevel(factor(ph_mapping_data_unshifted$Variable), c("Unmapped", "Duplicates", "Unique"))

scientific <- function(x) {
  ifelse(x == 0, "0", parse(text = gsub("[+]", "", gsub("e", " %*% 10^", scientific_format()(x)))))
}

sample_order <- c("NGS1","NGS2","NGS3","NGS4","NGS5","NGS6","NGS7","NGS8")

ph_Fig1_read_mapping <- ph_mapping_data_unshifted %>%
  mutate(sample_name = case_when(
    sample_name == "NGS1_S1" ~ "NGS1",
    sample_name == "NGS2_S7" ~ "NGS2",
    sample_name == "NGS3_S2" ~ "NGS3",
    sample_name == "NGS4_S8" ~ "NGS4",
    sample_name == "NGS5_S3" ~ "NGS5",
    sample_name == "NGS6_S4" ~ "NGS6",
    sample_name == "NGS7_S5" ~ "NGS7",
    sample_name == "NGS8_S6" ~ "NGS8"
  )) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = sample_name, y = Reads, fill = Variable)) +
  geom_bar(position = "stack", stat = "identity") +
  theme_ms() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 60, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(fill = "", y = "# Reads", x = "", title = "Read mapping of 5-8 with wt+h") +
  theme(legend.position = "right") +
  scale_y_continuous(
    expand = c(0, 10000),
    labels = scientific
  ) +
